v:4 c:$ m:T02-unify-accent-tokens role:dev x:vue3/css
gate: LOCKED

task: Unify the split Logic-blue / taskboard-violet accents into one accent token set

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/styles/logic-pro.css
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/styles/glass.css

context: |
  Two accent languages currently fight:
    logic-pro.css : --lp-accent #4a90d9 (blue), focus ring rgba(74,144,217,.25)
    glass blobs   : violet 124,58,237 / indigo 79,70,229
    taskboard SoT : indigo 99,101,241, violet 138,92,246

  Decision: adopt taskboard's INDIGO/VIOLET as the shared accent voice while
  keeping Logic's neutral greys for chrome. The blue --lp-accent becomes violet
  so active states, focus, selection, and glass glow all speak one color.

new-tokens (add to :root in logic-pro.css):
  --lp-accent:        #7c5cff   /* violet — replaces #4a90d9 */
  --lp-accent-hover:  #8f74ff
  --lp-accent-rgb:    124, 92, 255
  /* keep --lp-record / --lp-play / --lp-danger as-is (semantic transport colors) */

steps:
  1. In logic-pro.css :root, change --lp-accent / --lp-accent-hover to the violet
     values above and add --lp-accent-rgb.
  2. Replace hard-coded blue focus glows with the token:
       .lp-input:focus / .lp-select:focus box-shadow →
         0 0 0 2px rgba(var(--lp-accent-rgb), 0.30)
       (search logic-pro.css for rgba(74,144,217 and #4a6fa5 / #2a5f8f and
        re-point them to the accent token / a violet equivalent).
  3. In glass.css, align the violet blob + any glow vars to the SAME violet hue
     family so backdrop, glass glow, and accent agree. Do NOT change the neutral
     glass surface greys (--glass-bg*).
  4. .lp-track.selected highlight: re-tint from blue (74,111,165) to
     rgba(var(--lp-accent-rgb), 0.40).

done:
  - Grep for 4a90d9 / 74,144,217 / 4a6fa5 / 2a5f8f in logic-pro.css → all
    re-pointed to accent token or violet (no stray Logic-blue accents).
  - Focus rings, .active buttons, selected track, editor-tool.active all violet.
  - Glass blobs/glow share the violet hue family.
  - DAW neutral greys (panel/input/border tokens) untouched.
  - No new compile/CSS errors.
